==English==
===Etymology===
First attested in [[w:1606|1606]], from Greek εὐϑανασία (euthanasia), from εὐ- (eu-) good + ϑάνατος (thanatos), death
<br>

===Pronunciation===
*yo͞o"thənā'zhə, /ˌjuːθəˈneɪʒə/, /<tt>%ju:T@"neIZ@</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-euthanasia.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-unc}}
{{wikipedia}}

#The [[practice]] of [[kill]]ing a [[human being]] or animal who is suffering greatly or has very poor [[quality of life]], especially one with an [[incurable]] [[illness]] or [[condition]].
#:'''''Euthanasia''' is the hardest part of a veterinarian's job.''
#(''as a modifier'') Of or relating to euthanasia.
#: ''The veterinary technician pulled the '''euthanasia''' solution from the controlled drug cabinet.''

